Text: This week we were assigned a project to work on Wednesday 13th.
Our assigned project is to help improve interactivity at the Otago Museum.
They propose that this is done by having QR codes that can be scanned by mobile devices that direct the device to a webpage that displays information and or videos about the relevant exhibits.
We have a meeting with the client set for Monday 18th at 4pm, once this has happened we should gain a better understanding of the project and everything that the client hopes we can achieve.
I've taken on a team leader role because of my prior experience during my BIT at Otago Polytechnic.
I'm hoping to learn a fair bit about managing a team during my time on this project.
Because of our limited knowledge about the project at this point the only work we have done so far is to set up our team processes.
I've set up a Slack channel for us to communicate on.
I also set up a Discord channel for our meetings and collaborative work because this is a free software and Slack seemed to require a fee to allow group calls.
I have also set up a Trello page for us to manage the projects tasks through.
We have some collaborative Google Docs set up so that we can work through our project proposal and record questions and answers that we have for our client.
I think so far this is a good start for the group given the limited information we have so far.
Next week will be more productive.
